EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to contractors; increasing the value of certain
work a licensed contractor may perform for which the
contractor does not have a license in the applicable
classification or subclassification; and providing other
matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law authorizes a licensed contractor to perform work of a type for
2 which the contractor does not have a license in the applicable classification or
3 subclassification if: (1) the value of the work is less than $1,000, including labor
4 and materials; (2) the work does not require a permit; and (3) the work is not of a
5 type performed by a plumbing, electrical, refrigeration or air-conditioning
6 contractor. (NRS 624.220) This bill increases the value of work that a licensed
7 contractor may perform for which the contractor does not have a license in the
8 applicable classification or subclassification from less than $1,000 to less than
9 $2,500.
